                        	<h4 style="color: olive;" ><a name="about">Mobile Buddy</a></h4>
                            
                            <h6 style="font-size: 15px; color:gray;">This is a mobile version of the 
                            app which helps you to play a role like timer, grammarian during the meeting and 
                            help you organize your speech notes, table topics and plan better for your meetings and more.. </h6>
                        	<hr/>
                        	<br/>
                        	<h4 style="color: olive;"><a name="features">Features</a></h4>
                        	<h5 style="color: olive;">Organize Meetings</h5>
                            <table><tr><td></table><img width="350px" height="350px"  src="./theme/green/images/screenCaps/meetingList.png" alt=""></td>
                            <td><img width="350px" height="350px"  src="./theme/green/images/screenCaps/meetingAction.png" alt=""></td></table>
                            <h6 style="font-size: 15px; color:gray;">You can create current meetings and plan for the future meetings. There will be a log 
                            of all the meetings and you can always come back to see what happened during the meetings. You can add a new meeting using the '+' icon
                            at the top or browse the previous or current meeting by clicking on the specific meeting.</h6>
                            <br/>
                        	<h5 style="color: olive;">Timer</h5>
                            <figure class="p2"><img width="350px" height="350px"  src="./theme/green/images/screenCaps/timer.png" alt=""></figure>
                            <h6 style="font-size: 15px; color:gray;">You can use the timer to keep track of the time for any speech, table topic or other public speaking at the meeting either for yourself, or time it for 
                            another member with a role. The timer has a feature where you can specify time limits, which can be used to Signal Green, Yellow and Red colors. The app alerts you with changing colors based on the times you have specified so that you can 
                            flag the speaker. If you are not a timer you can log your time taken for various types of speech and keep track of your progress.
                            </h6>
                            <br/>
                        	<h5 style="color: olive;">Grammarian</h5>
                            <figure class="p2"><img width="350px" height="350px"  src="./theme/green/images/screenCaps/grammarian.png" alt=""></figure>
                            <h6 style="font-size: 15px; color:gray;">Using the mobile app you can play the role of a grammarian during
                            the meeting and count the number of ah, amms etc for the speaker. In case you want to add another counter, you can do so too. If you are not a grammarian, you can log your amCounts to 
                            keep track of your progress </h6>
                            <br/>
                            <h5 style="color: olive;">Speaker</h5>
                            <figure class="p2"><img width="350px" height="350px"  src="./theme/green/images/screenCaps/cardList.png" alt=""></figure>
                            <h6 style="font-size: 15px; color:gray;">This app can help you better present your speech by having your notes in your hands. 
                            You can use the built in flash cards to easily flip them and read your notes while giving your speech.
                            </h6>
                            <br>
                        	<h5 style="color: olive;">Table Topics</h5>
                            <figure class="p2"><img width="350px" height="350px"  src="./theme/green/images/screenCaps/cardList.png" alt=""></figure>
                            <h6 style="font-size: 15px; color:gray;">
                            You can write all your table topics on the flash cards and flip them while asking them during the meeting. This easy to use interface
                            makes it fun to ask table topics</h6>
                        	<h5 style="color: olive;">History</h5>
                            <figure class="p2"><img width="350px" height="350px"  src="./theme/green/images/screenCaps/myLog.png" alt=""></figure>
                            <h6 style="font-size: 15px; color:gray;">
                            The application keeps a log of all your club activity. At any time you can go back and view what roles you played in the meetings, check how you are doing with amCounts and timelimits.
                            This is a great tool to keep track of your progress and understand how well you are doing overtime.</h6>
                        	<h5 style="color: olive;">Nervous Test</h5>
                            <figure class="p2"><img width="350px" height="350px"  src="./theme/green/images/screenCaps/nervous.png" alt=""></figure>
                            <h6 style="font-size: 15px; color:gray;">This feature will help you test how nervous you are, but might still bring a smile to your face :). Its a good one to check before going up for your
                            first speech or host the meeting!</h6>
